&lt;h3&gt;Quarks,leptons and the big bang&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Quarks, leptons and the big bang is a clear, readable and self contained introduction to particle physics and related areas of cosmology. It bridges the gap between non technical popular accounts and textbooks for advanced students. The book concentrates on presenting the subject from the modern perspective or quarks, leptons and the forces between them.This approach enables readers to grasp the essential concepts more easily than the traditional historical approach involving the complex interaction of hadrons. It then moves on to applying these ideas to modern cosmology.&lt;/p&gt;
